cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on the problem of integrating cross-OSN information for social media search, which involves information retrieval (IR) and social media analysis. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a framework for hashtag representation, clustering, and demonstration, which involves multimedia analysis and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely sub-categories.
